snippet.textDisplay:
I just thought of something... What if a new survival open-world destiny game was made set in the time of the savage warlords before the last city. There's a lot of interesting lore tied into this time period that could make for an amazing game. It could even be multiplayer. Imagine waking up like Zavala in his cutscene trailer with a sword or spear trying to survive in the mountains against other people fighting for territory. With the new gaming tech etc it should be possible. If this was done though, it would be smart to also add the third person as a second alternative, because the game could be made so cinematic in the unforgiving landscape that we have traversed through during the red war. You'd be able to make settlements, be a warlord yourself, be a warrior of the light, or just fend off for yourself and survive. Crafting could than also be a neat mechanic. You could then also make melee combat a larger focus. With this, I mean focus on the mechanics that are tied in with melee combat, and maybe finishers to keep the flow of combat persistent. I know that I'm just a random guy on the internet, but this could make for an amazing game. If Bungie at least sees this, I'll be really happy.
Source of some of the inspiration of my post: https://youtu.be/FxRFbg8NaCs
I also got inspiration for this after playing the first mission of the red war again
And finally, I got inspiration from the lore books in-game.
